HEADWORD: Proficiency
<hw>Pro*fi"cien*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of state of being
proficient; advance in the acquisition of any art, science, or
knowledge; progression in knowledge; improvement; adeptness; <as>as, to
acquire <ex>proficiency</ex> in music</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

